            "title": "Prompt 1",
            "properties": {
              "text": "{\n  \"scene\": 1,\n  \"title\": \"THE FRUSTRATION + EVIDENCE\",\n  \"timing\": \"0:00-0:08\",\n  \"duration\": \"8s\",\n  \"reference_frame\": \"scene-01-02-05-image-start.json (lab/development workspace)\",\n  \"profile\": \"default (modified: 165 WPM, high energy)\",\n  \"script_segment\": \"I used to dread shaving. Every time — bumps, irritation, ingrowns.\",\n  \"word_count\": 10,\n  \"speech_duration\": \"~3.6s\",\n  \"visual_beat\": \"~4.4s silent after dialogue\",\n\n  \"visual\": \"Static camera shot. Front-facing, eye level. She speaks directly to camera with natural frustration — the kind of energy you'd have venting to a friend. She holds a traditional razor loosely in her right hand. Natural hand gestures while talking — nothing choreographed, just the way someone moves when they're telling a story they're annoyed about. On 'bumps, irritation, ingrowns' she gestures with the razor hand for emphasis. After she finishes speaking, she drops the razor onto the counter and runs her hand along her forearm with a slight wince. Looks back at camera with a 'you know what I mean' expression.\",\n\n  \"audio\": \"DIALOGUE: \\\"I used to dread shaving. Every time — bumps, irritation, ingrowns.\\\"\\n\\nDELIVERY: Conversational but energized, 165 WPM. Real frustration, not performative — like telling a friend about a recurring annoyance. Emphasis on 'dread' and the list of 'bumps, irritation, ingrowns.' General American accent. After dialogue ends, 4.4 seconds of silence with ambient room tone only.\",\n\n  \"negative_prompt\": \"camera movement, shaky cam, zooming, panning, dolly shots, tracking shots, handheld movement, monotone voice, flat affect, robotic speech, whispered speech, professional narrator voice, cartoonish eyes, bug eyes, exaggerated expressions, sound effects, whooshes, background music, ambient noise, fake excitement, infomercial style, shouting\",\n\n  \"prompt\": \"Static camera shot. Front-facing, eye level. She speaks directly to camera with natural frustration, venting to a friend. Holds a traditional razor loosely in her right hand. Natural hand gestures while talking. On 'bumps, irritation, ingrowns' she gestures with the razor for emphasis. After speaking, she drops the razor onto the counter and runs her hand along her forearm with a slight wince. Looks back at camera with a 'you know what I mean' expression.\\n\\nDIALOGUE: \\\"I used to dread shaving. Every time — bumps, irritation, ingrowns.\\\"\\n\\nDELIVERY: Conversational but energized, 165 WPM. Real frustration like telling a friend about a recurring annoyance. Emphasis on 'dread' and the list. General American accent. After dialogue, 4.4 seconds of silence with ambient room tone only.\\n\\nNegative prompt: camera movement, shaky cam, zooming, panning, dolly shots, tracking shots, handheld movement, monotone voice, flat affect, robotic speech, whispered speech, professional narrator voice, cartoonish eyes, bug eyes, exaggerated expressions, sound effects, whooshes, background music, ambient noise, fake excitement, infomercial style, shouting\"\n}",
