            "title": "Prompt 8",
            "properties": {
              "text": "{\n  \"scene\": 2,\n  \"title\": \"THE ORIGIN\",\n  \"timing\": \"0:08-0:14\",\n  \"duration\": \"6s\",\n  \"reference_frame\": \"scene-01-02-05-image-start.json (lab/development workspace)\",\n  \"profile\": \"default (modified: 165 WPM, high energy)\",\n  \"script_segment\": \"I tried everything. Nothing worked. So I thought — why don't I just make my own?\",\n  \"word_count\": 15,\n  \"speech_duration\": \"~5.5s\",\n  \"visual_beat\": \"~0.5s held reaction after dialogue\",\n\n  \"visual\": \"Static camera shot. Fixed angle, slightly wider framing than Scene 1. She starts frustrated — 'I tried everything' with an open palm sweep. 'Nothing worked' lands flat, maybe a small shrug or hands dropping. Then her energy shifts — 'So I thought' gets a little head tilt, a hint of a smile forming. 'Why don't I just make my own' is where the confidence arrives — she points at herself casually, a real smile breaks through. The kind of expression someone makes when they're proud of a bold decision. Quick nod at the end, cut.\",\n\n  \"audio\": \"DIALOGUE: \\\"I tried everything. Nothing worked. So I thought — why don't I just make my own?\\\"\\n\\nDELIVERY: 165 WPM. The energy shifts mid-scene — starts frustrated, ends confident. 'I tried everything' has weight. 'Nothing worked' is matter-of-fact. Then the tone lifts on 'So I thought' — she's getting to the good part. 'Make my own' lands with pride and a smile in her voice. General American accent.\",\n\n  \"negative_prompt\": \"camera movement, shaky cam, zooming, panning, dolly shots, tracking shots, handheld movement, monotone voice, flat affect, robotic speech, whispered speech, professional narrator voice, cartoonish eyes, bug eyes, exaggerated expressions, sound effects, whooshes, background music, ambient noise, fake excitement, infomercial style, shouting\",\n\n  \"prompt\": \"Static camera shot. Fixed angle, slightly wider framing. She starts frustrated — 'I tried everything' with an open palm sweep. 'Nothing worked' lands flat, small shrug. Energy shifts — 'So I thought' gets a head tilt, hint of smile. 'Why don't I just make my own' — she points at herself, real smile breaks through. Quick nod, cut.\\n\\nDIALOGUE: \\\"I tried everything. Nothing worked. So I thought — why don't I just make my own?\\\"\\n\\nDELIVERY: 165 WPM. Shifts from frustrated to confident mid-scene. 'I tried everything' has weight. 'Nothing worked' is matter-of-fact. Tone lifts on 'So I thought.' 'Make my own' lands with pride and a smile. General American accent.\\n\\nNegative prompt: camera movement, shaky cam, zooming, panning, dolly shots, tracking shots, handheld movement, monotone voice, flat affect, robotic speech, whispered speech, professional narrator voice, cartoonish eyes, bug eyes, exaggerated expressions, sound effects, whooshes, background music, ambient noise, fake excitement, infomercial style, shouting\"\n}",
