            "title": "Prompt 8",
            "properties": {
              "text": "{\n  \"style_mode\": \"raw_photoreal_high_fidelity\",\n  \"look\": \"social media realism, smartphone aesthetic, UGC B-roll for Meta ads\",\n  \"aspect_ratio\": \"9:16 vertical\",\n  \"broll_id\": 3,\n  \"broll_title\": \"SHAVING FRUSTRATION — END FRAME\",\n  \"used_in\": \"Video Plan Scene 2 — THE EVIDENCE (Shot C)\",\n  \"delta_from\": \"broll-03-image-start.json\",\n  \"requires\": [],\n\n  \"camera\": {\n    \"change_from_start\": \"same handheld POV angle looking down at her leg. Same casual framing, same bathtub edge visible\"\n  },\n\n  \"scene\": {\n    \"subject\": {\n      \"change_from_start\": \"the razor is now set down on the bathtub edge beside her leg — she's stopped mid-routine. The shin where she just passed shows a visible stripe of redness and irritation along the razor's path, clearly contrasting with the untouched skin around it. Her free hand is now touching the irritated area lightly with her fingertips, checking the damage. The contrast between the red irritated stripe and the normal surrounding skin is obvious\"\n    }\n  },\n\n  \"narrative_prompt\": \"Same casual smartphone POV looking down at her leg on the bathtub edge, but the routine has stopped. The disposable razor is set down on the bathtub rim beside her. Her shin shows a clear stripe of redness and irritation along the path where the razor just went — obvious contrast against the normal surrounding skin. Her free hand touches the irritated area lightly with her fingertips, feeling the damage. Same handheld quality, same bathroom setting, same UGC energy. The moment you stop shaving because it's clearly making things worse.\"\n}\n",
